genresAdvancedInfo.name: free improvisation
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Free improvisation is a genre of music that involves spontaneous creation of music without any pre-planned structure or composition. It is a form of musical expression that is completely free from any rules or guidelines, allowing the musicians to explore their creativity and take risks. The focus is on the process of creating music rather than the end result, resulting in unique and unpredictable performances.
